        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 4:45PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 445 PM EDT, a strong thunderstorm was over Blackjack Mountain, or
12 miles southwest of Carrollton, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
Carrollton, Villa Rica, Bremen, Temple, Bowdon, Mount Zion,
Whitesburg, Ephesus, Roopville, Byers Crossroads, Bowdon Junction,
Hannah, Tyus, Seaton Lake, Fairplay, Clem, Abilene, Lake Val-Do-Mar,
John Tanner State Park, and Lowell.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
